<h1>Lessons to Be Learned from the Pandemic</h1>

<p>
  <strong>Event:</strong> Online panel discussion<br>
  <strong>Date:</strong> 28 November 2022
</p>

<h3>Overview</h3>

<p>
This panel discussion reflected on the academic, social, and personal lessons emerging from
the COVID-19 pandemic. Speakers discussed its impact on research practices, mobility,
work–life balance, and inequalities in academia.
</p>

<h3>Speakers</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Marta Rivera</strong>, University of Granada, Spain &amp; Fulbright Scholar at University of California, Irvine, USA</li>
  <li><strong>Ana B. Chica</strong>, University of Granada, Spain</li>
  <li><strong>Kalinka Timmer</strong>, University of Warsaw, Poland</li>
  <li><strong>Gabriella Vigliocco</strong>, University College London, UK</li>
</ul>

<h3>Chairs</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>María J. Maraver</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Nura Sidarus</strong></li>
</ul>

